Mind also fixing this kind of stuff while you're at it?
```suggestion

* We show that the age of any structure is isomorphism-invariant and satisfies the hereditary and
```
I've looked over the style guides again, and generalized to trying to match the current style.
I thought people were normalising to using `*` for the outside bullet list? Maybe I'm wrong

The official style guide uses `-`, for what I believe is still this case.
https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/style.html

I'm happy to use either, but I want a reference to follow.
